"Security has always been a difficult sell within organisations. Those responsible for the safety and integrity of an organisation's data have to fight for budget yet often lack the killer argument that would help them secure funds – a tangible benefit to the company's bottom line. In other words, how can security help a firm make more money? In this interview, Colin Tankard, managing director of Digital Pathways, argues that, in fact, it is perfectly reasonable to talk about a Return on Investment (ROI) from the money spent on security capabilities – if you know how to measure it."
